SimSwarm's design was informed by two earlier projects:

  - MiroFish
  - MiroShark — https://github.com/aaronjmars/MiroShark

Both are licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0).

SimSwarm does not bundle, link, or depend on either project, and shares no
source code with them. SimSwarm's engine is an independent, MIT-licensed
implementation. Several concepts were validated first in MiroFish/MiroShark and
were reimplemented from a behavioral specification in SimSwarm's own code:

  - heuristic, per-agent belief dynamics (stance / confidence / trust)
  - constant-product prediction-market mechanics
  - the agent / environment simulation loop

We credit those projects for the conceptual groundwork. Any resemblance is at
the level of ideas and behavior, not copied source.
